    "created_at": "2026-01-06T14:41:33Z",
    "updated_at": "2026-01-06T14:43:05Z",
    "body": "It would be great to be able to configure styles dynamically, to change the color of any module based on a shell env var (with a default if not set) - My use case is to set a different $hostname style based on which host I am on (I use the same starship config on all my servers, synced with syncthing)\n\nOr maybe set the palette value dynamically? \n```\npalette = \"$SOME_SHELL_ENV_VAR_PALETTE_NAME\"\n```\n\nor add a palette flag when activating the prompt?\n```\neval \"$(starship init bash --palette foo)\"\n```",
